# Firebase / Firestore

## Collections (under `/users/{uid}/`)

| Collection | Notes |
|------------|-------|
| `users/{uid}` | `dailyCalorieTarget`, profile fields |
| `meals/{mealId}` | `date`, `slot`, `text`, `calories`, `breakdown[]`, `caloriesSource` |
| `weights/{date}` | **Document ID = `YYYY-MM-DD`** — upsert = one entry per day |
| `estimationCache/{normalizedText}` | **Document ID = normalized Hebrew text** |

## Slots

`BREAKFAST` | `LUNCH` | `DINNER` | `SNACK` — English labels in UI only.

## Security

```javascript
allow read, write: if request.auth != null && request.auth.uid == uid;
```

Deploy rules only after Rules Playground tests. Optional: hardcode allowed UID.

## Client patterns

- `onSnapshot` for today/meals by `date`; unsubscribe on unmount.
- Typed converters or mappers: Firestore camelCase fields match PRD (`reasoningHe`, `portionGrams`, etc.).
- Composite index required: meals `(date, slot)`.

## Do not

- Store Anthropic responses without Zod validation.
- Use client-computed "today" string for cross-midnight persistence without server alignment.
